      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented V&V history and version control meets MRL 2 requirement.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 was used under a documented software quality plan. Version control logs and regression test records are archived. Achieved level exceeds the MRL 2 requirement of Gradation 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard benchmark cases (lid-driven cavity, Poiseuille flow) at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver was verified against the lid-driven cavity benchmark (Re=1000) and fully-developed pipe-flow (Poiseuille) benchmarks. Numerical errors were within 0.5% of analytical solutions, satisfying the Gradation 1 requirement with margin."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for hemolysis index QoI; GCI < 5% on fine mesh.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the impeller passage. GCI for the normalized hemolysis index was 3.2% on the fine mesh (9.4 M cells), satisfying the Gradation 2 requirement. The medium mesh (4.7 M cells) was selected for production runs based on cost-accuracy trade-off."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) match simulation boundary conditions within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data were collected at five flow-speed operating points. Measured boundary conditions (inlet flow rate 2–8 L/min, speed 2500–3500 RPM, blood analog viscosity) were reproduced in the CFD model within ±2.1%, satisfying the Gradation 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predicted within 20% of experimental values across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values were within 12% of experimental measurements across all five operating points, with mean absolute error of 8.4%. The model systematically over-predicts hemolysis at low flow rates by up to 11%, which is conservative for worst-case identification. Achieves Gradation 3 (quantitative agreement with uncertainty bounds)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the clinical endpoint used in the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate is the primary regulatory QoI per FDA guidance. The CFD model outputs volumetric shear stress history integrated via the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model to yield NIH, which directly populates RH. Full traceability from model output to decision criterion is documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments use the same pump geometry and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under CPB operating conditions (2–8 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM), which spans the COU envelope. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, matched viscosity) was used in both validation and COU simulations. Geometric and operational relevance is high."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residuals converge to at least 1e-5 for all transport equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All steady-state RANS simulations converged to residuals below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum, and 1e-7 for turbulence quantities. Global mass imbalance was below 0.005%. Satisfies Gradation 1 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; documented analyst training records suffice.",
      "rationale": "At Model Risk Level 2, formal use-error assessment is not required. Analyst qualifications (PhD-level CFD training, 5+ years pump simulation experience) are documented in the project record. Gradation 1 is satisfied by qualification records alone."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified; hemolysis sub-model applicability documented.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on published literature for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model was benchmarked against erythrocyte fragility data. Model form uncertainty is acknowledged in the UQ report, which describes a screening sensitivity study comparing SST k-omega versus realizable k-epsilon; however, this screening is reported narratively and no formal structured sensitivity analysis record is linked. Achieves Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties sourced from traceable measurements or published standards; uncertainty bounds reported.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles derived from ultrasonic flow meter measurements (±1.5%). Blood analog viscosity measured via cone-and-plate rheometry at 37°C (±3%). Rotational speed from encoder data (±0.2%). The UQ report documents propagation of these input uncertainties through the model using a Monte Carlo approach with 200 samples, yielding 95% confidence intervals on NIH. A screening sensitivity study is mentioned in the UQ narrative to identify which inputs most influence NIH, but the dominant driver ranking is described in prose only and no hasSensitivityAnalysis record is formally linked to this assurance package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; single pump specimen used in validation is acceptable.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, sample-to-sample variability assessment is not required. A single FDA generic pump specimen was used for validation experiments. Gradation 1 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; documented correspondence between validation and COU inputs is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal equivalency scoring is not required. Correspondence between validation experiment inputs and COU simulation inputs is documented in the test plan. Gradation 1 is satisfied by documentation."
    }
  ],
